statistical performance¶

In [308]:
## Single function to obtain the statistical performance measures

def get_stat_performance(df):

    # mean bias
    
    mb_pblh = (df['mod_pbl'] - df['obs_pbl']).describe()[1]
    
    print("Stat performance :\n")
    print("mean bias pblh = ", mb_pblh)
    
    # Fractional bias
    
    fb_pblh = 2 * ((df['mod_pbl'].describe()[1] - df['obs_pbl'].describe()[1]) / \
                   (df['mod_pbl'].describe()[1] + df['obs_pbl'].describe()[1]))
    
    print("fractional bias pblh = ", fb_pblh)
          
    # pearson's corr coeff.
    
    r_pblh = ((df['obs_pbl'] - df['obs_pbl'].describe()[1]) * \
              (df['mod_pbl'] - df['mod_pbl'].describe()[1])).describe()[1] / (df['mod_pbl'].describe()[2] * \
                                                                                 df['obs_pbl'].describe()[2])
    print("corr coeff pblh = ", r_pblh)
          
    # RMSE
    
    rmse_pblh = np.sqrt(((df['mod_pbl']-df['obs_pbl'])*(df['mod_pbl']-df['obs_pbl'])).describe()[1])
          
    print("rmse pblh = ", rmse_pblh)
